    <main>
      <div class="introduction">
        <h2>What is a Laplace Transform?</h2>
        <p> It's obviously given in the equation book as the following <span set:html={K(String.raw`F(s) = \int{e^{-st}f(t)} {dt}`)}> </span> but what does this mean and where does it come from
        </p>
        <p> Let's look at a simple function <span set:html={K(String.raw`f(t)`)}> </span> where <span set:html={K(String.raw`f(t)`)}> </span> is analytic so then the Taylor series can be represented by <span set:html={K(String.raw`
f(t) = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{f^{(n)}(0)}{n!} t^n
`)}></span> then we can let <span set:html={K(String.raw`a(n) = \frac{f^{(n)}(0)}{n!}`)} > </span> so that now <span set:html={K(String.raw`
f(t) = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} a(n) t^n
`)}> 

</p>
        
      </div>
      <div class="problem_introduction"> 
        <p> if you have a linear system <span set:html={K(String.raw`L[y] = g(t)`)}> </span> where g(t) is a piece wise function we would normally have to solve two diffrent intervals seperately </p>
        <li> 
            eg. see the following problem 
            <span set:html={K(String.raw`g(t) =
\begin{cases}
\text{2.4} & \text{0<t<10} \\
\text{1.2} & \text{t>10} \\

\end{cases}`)}> </span> then logically <span set:html={K(String.raw`x'(t) +3x/500 = g(t) \text{ let's assume that } x(0) = 30`)}> </span>
            </li>
        <li> 

            To solve this we must observe that an integrating factor of the form <span set:html={K(String.raw`\mu = e^{3/500*t}`)}> </span> then multiplying this to both sides it becomes <span set:html={K(String.raw`\frac{d} {dt} (e^{3/500*t} x(t)) = e^{3/500*t}g(t)`)}> </span> then we integrate to get <span set:html={K(String.raw`x(t) = (\int{ e^{3/500*t}g(t) dt})/ e^{3t/500}`)}> </span>now we would have to plug in two g(t)'s and solve to get a piecewise result for x
            </li>
        </div>
        <h2>Excercises</h2>
        <div class="exercise">
        <h3>1. apply laplace transform to this <span set:html={K(String.raw`f(t) =
\begin{cases}
\text{3} & \text{0<= t <= 2} \\
\text{6-t} & \text{2<t} \\

\end{cases}`)}> </span> </h3>
        <p> We need to use the unit step function to represent <span set:html={K("f(t) = 3 + u(t-2)(3-t)")}> </span> then we appy the laplace transform <span set:html={K(String.raw`
    \mathcal{L}\{ f(t) \} = \mathcal{L}\{ 3\} + \mathcal{L}\{ u(t-2)(3-t)\} 
    = \int_0^\infty 3 e^{-st} \, dt + \int_2^\infty (3-t) e^{-st} \, dt
    = 3/s + \int_2^\infty (3-t) e^{-st} \, dt
  `)} />
</p>

<p>
  Now this integral is tricky, so we can do it by substitution: 
  <span set:html={K(`\\text{let } w = t-2`)} /> then logically <span set:html={K(String.raw`t = w + 2 \text{ since if } t = 2 \text{ then } w = 0 \text{ logically the integral becomes } \int_0^\infty (1-w) e^{-s(w+2)} \, dw = e^{-2s}\int_0^\infty (1-w) e^{-ws)} \, dw` )}> </span></p> 
  <p> 
    Now we can do some splitting <span set:html={K(String.raw`e^{-2s}\int_0^\infty (1) e^{-ws} \, dw - e^{-2s}\int_0^\infty (w) e^{-ws)} \, dw = e^{-2s}* (1/s - 1/s^{2})  = F(s)`)}> </span>
    
    
</p>
<p> 

    <span set:html={K(String.raw` F(s) = e^{-2s} (1/s - 1/s^{2}) `)}> </span>
</p>
      </div>

      <h3> Laplace transforms and inverses are mainly just tabling to be honest so we'll do something more intresting. 

        Solve these IVP's
      </h3>
      <div class="exercise">
  <h3>Physical Interpretation Problem</h3>
 <h5> suppose there's an equation <span set:html={K("y'' - 7y' + 10y = 0; y(0) = 0; y'(0) = -3")}> </span> solve it using laplace transforms </h5>
 <p> Let's just transform both sides <span set:html={K(String.raw`\mathcal{L}\{ y''\} + \mathcal{L}\{ -7y' \} + \mathcal{L}\{ 10y\} = \mathcal{L}\{0\} = 0`)}> </span></p>
 <p> <span set:html={K(String.raw`s^{2}Y(s)−sy(0)−y′(0) -7sY(s) +7y(0) + Y(0) = 0  \text{ using our initial conditions and rearranging } Y(s)(s^{2}−7s+10)+3=0` )}> </span></p>
 <p> <span set:html={K(String.raw`Y(s) = \frac{-3}{(s-5)(s-2)}` )}> </span> Now we want to decompose fraction <span set:html={K(String.raw`−3=A(s−2)+B(s−5) A = -1; B =1 \text{ Now you just table to get } y(t) = e^{2t}−e^{5t}`)}> </span></p>


<div class="exercise">
  <h3>Physical Interpretation Problem</h3>
  <h5>
    Suppose there's a water tank where the inflow increases gradually after t = 1. The height of water \(y(t)\) is modeled by
    <span set:html={K("y'' + 2(t-1)y' - 2y = 0; y(0) = 0; y'(0) = 0")}> 
    </span>
    Solve it using Laplace transforms
  </h5>
  
  <p>
    Let's just transform both sides
    <span set:html={K(String.raw`\mathcal{L}\{y''\} + 2 \mathcal{L}\{(t-1)y'\} - 2 \mathcal{L}\{y\} = \mathcal{L}\{0\} = 0`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw`s^2 Y(s) - s y(0) - y'(0) + 2 \left(-\frac{d}{ds} [s Y(s) - y(0)] - Y(s)\right) - 2 Y(s) = 0`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw`s^2 Y(s) - 0 - 0 - 2\frac{d}{ds}[s Y(s)] - 2 Y(s) - 2 Y(s) = 0`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw` \text{Combine terms: } -2\frac{d}{ds}[s Y(s)] + s^2 Y(s) - 4 Y(s) = 0`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw` \text{Solve this first-order ODE for } Y(s) \text{ (separation of variables): } Y(s) = \frac{C}{s^2 (s+2)}`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw` \text{Now decompose fraction: } \frac{C}{s^2 (s+2)} = \frac{A}{s} + \frac{B}{s^2} + \frac{D}{s+2} , \text{ solve for constants}`)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <span set:html={K(String.raw` \text{Using Laplace table, invert to get } y(t) = B t + A + D e^{-2t} = \text{(linear term + exponential)} `)}> 
    </span>
  </p>
</div>
<div class="exercise">
  <h3>
    use laplace to solve this system 
    <span set:html={K("x' + y = 0; \\; x(0) = 0, \\; x + y' = 1 - u(t-2); \\; y(0) = 0")}></span>
  </h3>

  <div>So..., we do laplace both sides</div>

  <span set:html={K(String.raw`\mathcal{L}\{x' + y\} = 0`)}></span>

  <div></div>

  <span set:html={K(String.raw`
    \int_{0}^{\infty} x'(t)\, e^{-st}\, dt
    + 
    \int_{0}^{\infty} y(t)\, e^{-st}\, dt = 0
  `)}></span>
  <span set:html={K(String.raw`
\int_{0}^{\infty} x'(t)e^{-st}\,dt
`)}></span>

<div>Use integration by parts:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
u = e^{-st}, \quad dv = x'(t)\,dt
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
du = -s e^{-st}\,dt, \quad v = x(t)
`)}></span>

<div>Apply \(\int u\,dv = uv - \int v\,du\):</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\int_{0}^{\infty} x'(t)e^{-st}\,dt
= \left[ x(t)e^{-st} \right]_{0}^{\infty}
+ s \int_{0}^{\infty} x(t)e^{-st}\,dt
`)}></span>

<div>Evaluate the boundary term:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\left[ x(t)e^{-st} \right]_{0}^{\infty}
= 0 - x(0)
= -x(0)
`)}></span>

<div>Final result:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\int_{0}^{\infty} x'(t)e^{-st}\,dt
= s \int_{0}^{\infty} x(t)e^{-st}\,dt - x(0)
`)}></span>
<br> </br> 
<span set:html={K(String.raw`s\mathcal{L}\{x\} - x(0) + \mathcal{L}\{y\} = 0`)}></span>
<p>Since <span set:html={K(String.raw`x(0)= 0,`)}></span> 
    <br> </br> 
    
    <span set:html={K(String.raw`\mathcal{L}\{x' + y\} = 0 = s\mathcal{L}\{x \} +\mathcal{L}\{y \} ` )}></span></p>

    <div>Now take Laplace of the second equation:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\mathcal{L}\{x + y'\} = \mathcal{L}\{1 - u(t-2)\}
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\mathcal{L}\{x\} + \mathcal{L}\{y'\}
= \frac{1}{s} - \frac{e^{-2s}}{s}
`)}></span>

<div>Use the derivative rule:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\mathcal{L}\{y'\} = s\mathcal{L}\{y\} - y(0)
`)}></span>

<div>Since \(y(0)=0\):</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\mathcal{L}\{x\} + s\mathcal{L}\{y\}
= \frac{1 - e^{-2s}}{s}
`)}></span>

<div>So the system becomes:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
\begin{aligned}
sX + Y &= 0 \\
X + sY &= \frac{1 - e^{-2s}}{s}
\end{aligned}
`)}></span>

<div>Solve the system:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
Y = -sX
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
X + s(-sX) = \frac{1 - e^{-2s}}{s}
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
X(1 - s^2) = \frac{1 - e^{-2s}}{s}
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
X(s) = \frac{1 - e^{-2s}}{s(1 - s^2)}
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
Y(s) = -sX(s) = \frac{-(1 - e^{-2s})}{1 - s^2}
`)}></span>

<div>Prepare for inverse Laplace:</div>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
X(s) = \frac{1}{s(1 - s^2)} - \frac{e^{-2s}}{s(1 - s^2)}
`)}></span>

<span set:html={K(String.raw`
Y(s) = \frac{-1}{1 - s^2} + \frac{e^{-2s}}{1 - s^2}
`)}></span>

</div>

